



May it Please your Excellency
Chelsea [Mass.] August: 3d 1775



This covers the observation of the day to this time.1
Two ferry Boats Came on Shore at the ferry ways2 at 12 Last night with about 20 Passenger from Boston and the Signal upon Powder horn hill was Just Erected denoting more coming[.] am Just going down to the ferry.
Nothing Extraordinary Occurd Since I wrote Last I would beg leave to ask your Excellency whether I might attem[p]t to move the old wreck now on the ferry ways which greatly Obstructs
[217]
the Passenger in bringing up their good at Low water. I am your Excellencys Most obediant Humb. Servnt

Loammi Baldwin Liu. Col.

